    "short_descriptor": "Spanish Colonial + Mediterranean Revival, 1915-1940s, dominant in Florida residential.",
    "background_prose": "Mediterranean Revival emerged in Florida and California between 1915 and the 1940s, drawing on Spanish, Italian, and North African architectural traditions. In Florida, the style is essentially the default for high-end residential -- Addison Mizner's Palm Beach and Boca Raton work, Coral Gables, and most Florida-Mediterranean new builds trace back to this period. Key features include smooth stucco walls in cream or white, arched front entryways, decorative wrought-iron details, terracotta tile accents (traditional), and low-pitched roofs.",
