  "consider": {
    "kicker": "Things to consider · before you commit",
    "title_html": "Three things <em>most</em> homeowners forget.",
    "items": [
      {
        "number": "01.",
        "heading": "Mediterranean's defining roof material is traditionally terracotta barrel tile, not asphalt shingle.",
        "body": "Mediterranean's defining roof material is traditionally terracotta barrel tile, not asphalt shingle. Substituting asphalt for tile is common in Florida new builds for budget and weight reasons, but the substitution changes the silhouette. Pick a shingle color that approximates the tile palette (warm brown, weathered-wood, or a dedicated tile-look SKU like Tamko Lamarite Stone Coated Steel) to preserve the architectural intent."
      },
      {
        "number": "02.",
        "heading": "Charcoal is the safest mid-tone roof for resale.",
        "body": "Charcoal is the single most-installed asphalt color in the architectural category nationally, which means it appeals to the widest pool of resale buyers and translates across most home styles. If you are not strongly committed to a more decisive color (true black, weathered wood), charcoal is the lowest-risk choice."
      },
      {
        "number": "03.",
        "heading": "Install quality matters more than SKU.",
        "body": "All seven recommended SKUs hit Class A fire and 110-150 mph wind ratings. The bigger variable on a mediterranean elevation is install quality: ridge-line straightness, valley flashing, starter strip alignment. Insist on a Master Elite or equivalent certified contractor and a written workmanship warranty separate from the manufacturer's material warranty."
      }
    ]
  },
